    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-20T11:42:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-20T11:42:00-05:00" n="211"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/504: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shea</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-20T12:00:00-04:42">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 20, 1919, noon.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 9.25 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Strictly confidential. An unofficial report from the Foreign Office has reached
                    this Embassy to the effect that a mobilization of troops is taking place along
                    southern border of Peru and further that aeroplanes, arms and ammunition have
                    been received recently by the Peruvian Government from France and the United
                    States. It is suggested that the mobilization has been organized by Leguia for
                    the purpose of making demonstration against Chile.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shea</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
